1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,870
(Episode 134)

2
00:00:02,970 --> 00:00:05,380
Surrender is not an option for me.

3
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:08,610
Young Ja.

4
00:00:09,310 --> 00:00:11,980
I don't know what you think you know
about me to talk so recklessly,

5
00:00:13,420 --> 00:00:14,450
but do you know...

6
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:19,360
how hard I worked
serving CEO Chae to get to this position?

7
00:00:21,490 --> 00:00:23,230
Are you going to just look back
at the road you've traveled...

8
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:26,500
and throw the rest of your future
in the trash?

9
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,370
Stop looking back.

10
00:00:29,170 --> 00:00:33,440
Just look ahead to the life you can have
with Jun Ho, please.

11
00:00:33,510 --> 00:00:36,110
From now on, don't act like
you know anything about my son.

12
00:00:36,610 --> 00:00:38,210
I'll pretend I don't know you,

13
00:00:39,340 --> 00:00:41,210
so don't you ever interfere again.

14
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:52,160
That's why he transferred the land
for the Dream Hotel...

15
00:00:53,260 --> 00:00:55,130
to my father long ago...

16
00:00:56,130 --> 00:00:59,130
and entrusted all his stocks and assets
in Choi Ha Joon's name.

17
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,700
He told my father to hand them
over to you when you came of age.

18
00:01:02,370 --> 00:01:05,600
That's why my father
never filed your death certificate...

19
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,740
and kept waiting for you.

20
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:12,180
The true owner of Dream...

21
00:01:13,710 --> 00:01:14,710
is you.

22
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:21,550
The day you revealed
that you were Choi Ha Joon,

23
00:01:21,890 --> 00:01:24,220
my father called me, overjoyed.

24
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,360
He said his friend, Myung Chul,

25
00:01:26,660 --> 00:01:29,190
had sent his grandson to be with Jang Mi.

26
00:01:29,830 --> 00:01:33,360
You're a precious person to our family.

27
00:01:34,130 --> 00:01:35,200
To my father,

28
00:01:35,870 --> 00:01:37,270
to me, and to Suk Hee.

29
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,040
And especially to Jang Mi.

30
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:41,810
Thank you, Father.

31
00:01:42,610 --> 00:01:43,780
Thank you so much.

32
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:47,910
You've been through a lot all this time,
haven't you?

33
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:53,050
It's all okay now.

34
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:57,020
Baek Ho.

35
00:01:57,490 --> 00:01:59,990
Why are you crying? What's going on?

36
00:02:00,730 --> 00:02:01,730
Dad.

37
00:02:02,390 --> 00:02:04,330
Don't tell me you did this to him.

38
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:07,630
Are you taking
your husband's side already?

39
00:02:07,770 --> 00:02:10,170
No, Dad, that's not it.

40
00:02:11,170 --> 00:02:14,040
Jang Mi. It's because I'm so happy.

41
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:18,240
Your father just solved a problem
that's been weighing on me.

42
00:02:19,140 --> 00:02:20,650
A problem that's been weighing on you?

43
00:02:21,580 --> 00:02:24,120
It's like I'm being born again today.

44
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:26,520
Thank you, Jang Mi.

45
00:02:27,450 --> 00:02:28,590
Thank you, Father.

46
00:02:31,890 --> 00:02:32,890
What did you say?

47
00:02:33,530 --> 00:02:35,790
You're saying that you're Choi Ha Joon?

48
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:38,560
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you sooner,
Jang Mi.

49
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,160
You're saying you're...

50
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:43,770
Choi Ha Joon, the majority shareholder
of Dream Hotel?

51
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,640
Is that really true?

52
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:50,110
- Well...
- That's amazing.

53
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,740
- No...
- This is so great.

54
00:02:51,810 --> 00:02:54,880
Gosh. I didn't know
you got so excited about money.

55
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:56,580
Of course, I'm excited.

56
00:02:57,620 --> 00:03:00,790
And this will help us
take down Chae Hwa Young.

57
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,220
That's right.

58
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,960
It's great that you're rich.

59
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,890
I mean, who complains about having money?

60
00:03:06,490 --> 00:03:07,760
That's true.

61
00:03:09,490 --> 00:03:10,500
But,

62
00:03:10,930 --> 00:03:12,700
there's something
I still haven't told you.

63
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:16,470
What's been so hard for me...

64
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,570
is the fire incident
involving my grandfather.

65
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,840
It's just that...

66
00:03:22,610 --> 00:03:24,780
I thought it might be
connected to the Chairman.

67
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:28,380
I'm ashamed to say
I suspected the Chairman.

68
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:30,480
My grandfather?

69
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:34,290
But it wasn't him?

70
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:37,360
On the contrary, he was my benefactor.

71
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:39,760
That's a relief.

72
00:03:40,530 --> 00:03:45,260
Baek Ho.
You must have had such a hard time.

73
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,670
Not being able to tell me anything.

74
00:03:55,810 --> 00:03:58,810
My goodness,
so that was the story behind it all.

75
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:02,210
Gosh, I can finally breathe easy.

76
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:03,980
I was just so afraid that...

77
00:04:04,150 --> 00:04:07,650
my grandfather and the Chairman
might have been enemies.

78
00:04:08,050 --> 00:04:10,020
That would have made things awkward
for Jang Mi and me.

79
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,890
Right.

80
00:04:13,460 --> 00:04:15,190
It's Chae Hwa Young after all.

81
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:18,560
She drove a wedge between
Chairman Choi and Chairman Ma...

82
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,830
to steal your shares.

83
00:04:20,830 --> 00:04:22,670
That makes it harder to forgive her.

84
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:25,670
To think I doubted the Chairman,
even for a moment,

85
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,510
I feel so terrible and angry with myself.

86
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:31,280
Still, it's a huge relief
that we found out.

87
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,150
What?

88
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,580
You took out...

89
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:41,150
a five-million-dollar private loan
to get this?

90
00:04:41,790 --> 00:04:43,250
Why did you do that?

91
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:45,690
Why?

92
00:04:45,690 --> 00:04:49,430
I had to spend all this money cleaning up
your mess because you screwed up.

93
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:53,060
Lee Kang Hyuk, tell me the truth.

94
00:04:53,260 --> 00:04:55,130
You said you buried this in the mountains.

95
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:57,940
Then how did it end up
in Shin Ae Ran's hands?

96
00:04:58,900 --> 00:04:59,900
Spit it out.

97
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:03,140
Don't tell me you were
planning to betray me.

98
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:05,810
Betray you? No, of course not.

99
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:09,050
How could I betray you when I have my son,
Jun Ho, to think about?

100
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:11,680
Then why was the wrench
in Shin Ae Ran's hands?

101
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:13,350
And the audio file too.

102
00:05:15,450 --> 00:05:18,390
I was too ashamed to say anything.

103
00:05:20,530 --> 00:05:22,260
Ssangkal betrayed me too.

104
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:27,430
I hid the wrench,
but Ssangkal must have seen and stolen it.

105
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:29,900
Ssangkal must've given it
to Shin Ae Ran...

106
00:05:30,670 --> 00:05:33,840
before he went to prison.

107
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:35,140
Then what?

108
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:37,480
So you knew you'd been betrayed.

109
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:41,110
Is that why you had Ssangkal killed
in prison?

110
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:43,610
Not for me, but for yourself?

111
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:46,350
How was that for me? It was for you.

112
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:49,320
You're the one who hit Oh Bok Gil
with the wrench.

113
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,660
And Ssangkal took the fall
and went to prison for it.

114
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,760
To silence him,

115
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,830
you're the one who ordered me
to get rid of Ssangkal.

116
00:05:56,860 --> 00:05:58,060
Enough.

117
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:01,200
Let's not ruin the mood
by bringing that up.

118
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,010
What are you just sitting there for?

119
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,440
We need to get rid of this right now.

120
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:27,730
Now there's no evidence left.

121
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:30,360
This is really the end of it all.

122
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,500
Oh Jang Mi, Kang Baek Ho.

123
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:35,930
No matter how hard you try
to take me down,

124
00:06:36,770 --> 00:06:38,740
it will all be for nothing
without any evidence.

125
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:42,640
I'm completely in the clear now.

126
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:44,980
Perfectly innocent.

127
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:47,010
Right?

128
00:06:47,650 --> 00:06:48,650
That's right.

129
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:52,480
There is no evidence
that can hold you accountable.

130
00:06:54,490 --> 00:06:55,490
Wrong.

131
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:58,360
I have the real wrench.

132
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:34,530
Ssangkal, you punk.

133
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:38,260
You stole it without even knowing
it was fake.

134
00:07:39,530 --> 00:07:42,130
I was just testing your loyalty.

135
00:07:42,530 --> 00:07:43,630
You fool.

136
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:48,940
You just dug your own grave.

137
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,250
It's me.

138
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:56,980
Find someone with some pull
at the detention center.

139
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:59,180
Ssangkal.

140
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:02,090
That bastard betrayed me.

141
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:10,230
Ssangkal, that punk.

142
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:13,970
He didn't even know it was a fake wrench.

143
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:16,270
And he gave it to Shin Ae Ran
on his way to confess,

144
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:18,170
thinking it was some huge piece
of evidence?

145
00:08:35,220 --> 00:08:37,090
This is the real wrench, Chae Hwa Young.

146
00:08:37,890 --> 00:08:38,890
This...

147
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,830
is the proof you struck Oh Bok Gil.

148
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,610
This is just my insurance policy.

149
00:08:57,710 --> 00:08:59,840
You never know what might happen.

150
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:02,610
Just like how I took care of Ssangkal.

151
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:08,220
What did you say?
The wrench and the USB are gone?

152
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,120
Yes.

153
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:12,620
I got a call from Detective Kim
this morning.

154
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,590
He said the evidence vanished
without a trace.

155
00:09:15,330 --> 00:09:17,030
Seriously,
how could something like this happen?

156
00:09:17,260 --> 00:09:20,830
Chae Hwa Young must have a mole
inside the police station.

157
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,900
There's no other explanation.

158
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:24,300
That's right.

159
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,700
Chae Hwa Young has been able
to get away with things all this time...

160
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:29,270
because of a mole she planted high up.

161
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:31,880
If we want to make Chae Hwa Young
pay for her crimes,

162
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:34,650
we need to take care of all her moles
in the higher-ups first.

163
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:36,710
I'm so furious.

164
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,620
You worked up all that courage,

165
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:41,320
but what do we do now
that it was all for nothing?

166
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:43,650
We may have lost the wrench,

167
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,590
but I made a copy of the audio file.

168
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:50,560
I hope this can be of some help.

169
00:09:52,260 --> 00:09:54,630
Ae Ran, thank you.

170
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:58,600
With this, we'll uncover the truth
behind Noh Cheol Bong's death...

171
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:01,470
and make sure
Chae Hwa Young is brought to justice.

172
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:03,770
Yes, I'm counting on you.

173
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:10,210
What do we do?

174
00:10:10,650 --> 00:10:13,150
If we don't repay the 17 million dollars
by the day after tomorrow,

175
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:16,490
- we'll go into final bankruptcy.
- CEO Chae knows that too.

176
00:10:17,460 --> 00:10:18,460
Try not to panic.

177
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:20,590
But is there any way
to stop the bankruptcy?

178
00:10:21,690 --> 00:10:23,530
I'll meet all your conditions,

179
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:25,400
so just give me the 17 million dollars
right now.

180
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:28,670
I'll pay you the highest interest rate
in the private loan market.

181
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,900
Mr. Kim, you're the loan shark king
of this country,

182
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:34,440
and are you really nickel-and-diming me
over a measly 17 million dollars?

183
00:10:35,610 --> 00:10:37,380
I'm swimming in money,

184
00:10:37,410 --> 00:10:40,680
but I don't do anything
unless it's a sure thing.

185
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:48,290
If you put up just 5 percent of
your 15 percent in Dream Hotel's shares...

186
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:49,620
as collateral,

187
00:10:49,620 --> 00:10:53,790
I'll give you the 17 million dollars
in one lump sum.

188
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:55,590
You want me to use shares as collateral?

189
00:10:55,890 --> 00:10:56,890
Are you crazy?

190
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,200
The general shareholders' meeting is
right around the corner,

191
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:01,000
and you want me to hand over my shares
to a loan shark?

192
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:04,170
It's just collateral.

193
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:06,070
How can I lend you money
without collateral?

194
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:07,770
Still, it can't be my shares.

195
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:12,640
If you default the day after tomorrow,
forget the general shareholders' meeting.

196
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:16,650
This 15 percent stake?
It'll be as worthless as scrap paper.

197
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:19,050
You've miscalculated.

198
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:20,950
Well, it can't be helped.

199
00:11:21,590 --> 00:11:22,590
Wait.

200
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:25,020
Fine.

201
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:28,030
I'll put up five percent of my shares.

202
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:30,860
Deal.

203
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,230
Here's how the contract will work.

204
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,970
But add one special provision
to the contract.

205
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,940
"Until this general shareholders' meeting
is over,"

206
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:42,940
"the voting rights
for the collateral shares..."

207
00:11:43,210 --> 00:11:45,880
"will be exercised exclusively
and unconditionally by Chae Hwa Young."

208
00:11:47,810 --> 00:11:51,320
Just as you planned, Chairman.
She signed on the dotted line.

209
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:55,150
The 17 million dollars will be transferred
to Chae Hwa Young's account...

210
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:57,520
- by tomorrow morning.
- Good work, Mr. Kim.

211
00:11:57,820 --> 00:12:00,830
So, we've secured five percent
of Chae Hwa Young's shares.

212
00:12:01,130 --> 00:12:03,160
By the way,
she asked for a special provision...

213
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:06,000
to have exclusive voting rights
at the shareholders' meeting.

214
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:08,770
- Are you okay with that?
- It's just as I expected.

215
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:12,540
She wants to borrow the money,
but she won't give up the crown.

216
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:16,110
If she really becomes the chairman
of Dream Group,

217
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:19,680
how do you plan on taking
Chae Hwa Young's five percent stake?

218
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:23,410
It's right here
in the loan contract you wrote.

219
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:25,520
"The acceleration clause."

220
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:29,690
"If the debtor faces a critical issue
affecting their credit,"

221
00:12:29,690 --> 00:12:30,820
"such as a criminal arrest,"

222
00:12:31,260 --> 00:12:34,190
"the lender can immediately seize
the collateral shares..."

223
00:12:34,260 --> 00:12:36,030
"and forcibly liquidate them."

224
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:37,130
A poison pill provision.

225
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:38,400
This is all we need.

226
00:12:38,930 --> 00:12:40,760
Right, the poison pill provision.

227
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:45,570
She'll probably have to give up
her remaining ten percent stake...

228
00:12:45,570 --> 00:12:47,040
and go broke soon,

229
00:12:47,570 --> 00:12:48,570
so don't worry.

230
00:12:54,010 --> 00:12:55,110
What are you doing, Mom?

231
00:12:57,350 --> 00:13:00,250
We need to figure out
how to make a living now.

232
00:13:01,090 --> 00:13:03,220
I'll secretly sell this designer bag
of Hwa Young's...

233
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:04,590
and pocket the money for us.

234
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,790
We have no other choice.

235
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:08,090
What if you get caught?
She'll never let it slide.

236
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:10,690
She's already freaking out about having
no money and taking out private loans.

237
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,700
That's all the more reason we need to
find a way to survive.

238
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:14,870
Private loans?

239
00:13:15,070 --> 00:13:18,040
The interest on that
will snowball in no time,

240
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,640
and she'll end up on the street.

241
00:13:19,940 --> 00:13:23,610
Should we really be sitting around here,
just cooking meals at home?

242
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:25,780
You have a point.

243
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:32,820
Hey, what's going on?
Why do you have Hwa Young's bag?

244
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:35,920
It's nothing.
We were just looking at it. Right, Mom?

245
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:38,290
Of course. Gosh, well...

246
00:13:38,690 --> 00:13:41,390
I was just seeing
if this would match my outfit.

247
00:13:41,730 --> 00:13:45,730
I'm asking why you were about to walk off
with Hwa Young's bag.

248
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,200
My goodness, unbelievable.

249
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:51,770
What's it to you? Did you buy it for her?

250
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:53,440
Tell me, Professor Kang.

251
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,510
What's your relationship with Hwa Young?

252
00:13:55,810 --> 00:13:58,010
Are you really asking because you
don't know about Hwa Young and me?

253
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,680
Yes. I don't know.
I'm telling you I don't.

254
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:03,450
We're in love.
And we're going to get married.

255
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:06,480
- We're going to get married.
- That's what I thought.

256
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,250
You're about to get married.

257
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,050
You're not married yet, right?

258
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:14,190
Therefore, you and Hwa Young
are nothing to each other.

259
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:19,230
So, do you have the right
to meddle with me or not?

260
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:21,230
- Not.
- Right.

261
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,830
This house is always chaotic.

262
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,040
I brought steak,

263
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:28,270
but I guess I'll just cook and eat it
by myself. All alone.

264
00:14:28,340 --> 00:14:31,540
What? Steak?

265
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:35,950
Right. Did you look into Martin Jang?

266
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:38,820
But why are you asking about Martin Jang?

267
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:40,750
The 17 million dollars
from the private loan...

268
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:42,220
put out the immediate fire.

269
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:45,590
- What are you planning now?
- Jun Ho.

270
00:14:46,460 --> 00:14:48,630
Do you really think
I can achieve my dream...

271
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:51,800
by becoming the chairman of Dream?

272
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,670
- Well...
- You don't think I can either, do you?

273
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,170
Now that Jung Suk Hee is
Chairman Ma's biological daughter,

274
00:14:59,170 --> 00:15:02,870
no matter how hard I try,
Dream will never be mine.

275
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:04,780
In that case,

276
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:09,050
I might as well trample this flower garden
I've tended for 30 years,

277
00:15:09,050 --> 00:15:10,880
take what's mine, and leave.

278
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:12,180
Then...

279
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,990
are you really determined...

280
00:15:15,550 --> 00:15:16,790
to completely ruin Dream Hotel?

281
00:15:17,690 --> 00:15:21,360
I'll leave behind an empty shell
and take all the valuable parts with me.

282
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:24,560
I deserve to be paid
for my 30 years of work, don't I?

283
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:28,800
And that's why I need Martin Jang.

284
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:31,470
Tell me what you found out.

285
00:15:32,870 --> 00:15:35,840
Who does she think she is,
turning Dream into an empty shell?

286
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,640
Chae Hwa Young,
that's not going to happen.

287
00:15:39,140 --> 00:15:40,580
If anything,
the tables will be turned on you.

288
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:44,580
Martin Jang is backed
by a Chinese hedge fund...

289
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:47,380
and is a major player
operating in Europe and Singapore.

290
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:49,490
Meaning he has enormous capital.

291
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:53,360
I hear he's recently shown interest
in prime Asian companies.

292
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,060
A corporate raider.

293
00:15:55,490 --> 00:15:58,700
In that case,
he might be interested in our hotel.

294
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:01,030
He's a fearsome hunter
with an incredible nose...

295
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:03,000
for money.

296
00:16:03,570 --> 00:16:06,500
Good. If he's come sniffing for money,

297
00:16:06,770 --> 00:16:10,610
we need to throw him a piece of meat
he can really sink his teeth into.

298
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:14,550
Are you really going to sell Dream Hotel
to Martin Jang?

299
00:16:15,780 --> 00:16:16,780
No.

300
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:18,180
Then?

301
00:16:18,420 --> 00:16:21,490
Realistically, it's impossible
to hand over the entire hotel.

302
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:25,560
For now, the piece of meat I'll give
to Martin Jang...

303
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:27,490
is the heart of our hotel,

304
00:16:28,060 --> 00:16:30,130
the operating rights to the casino
and duty-free shop.

305
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:31,600
What?

306
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:36,470
But that's the goose
that lays the golden eggs.

307
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:40,170
If we give that up, our company
will be nothing but an empty shell.

308
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:44,440
For now, you just contact Martin Jang.
Tell him I'd like to see him.

309
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:46,380
Oh, really?

310
00:16:46,910 --> 00:16:48,680
So Chae Hwa Young has finally
taken the bait.

311
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:51,150
Got it.

312
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,720
Dad, did you hear from
Chae Hwa Young's side?

313
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:56,290
Yes.

314
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:59,620
Then it's your turn to make a move, Dad.

315
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,460
- Just you watch.
- Dad,

316
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:05,830
you're legally buying
the hotel's prime assets...

317
00:17:05,830 --> 00:17:09,370
at a competitive price
to save our hotel, right?

318
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,740
You're getting revenge
on Chae Hwa Young...

319
00:17:11,740 --> 00:17:13,500
and saving the hotel
from the brink of bankruptcy.

320
00:17:13,570 --> 00:17:16,370
You're killing two birds with one stone.
You're going to be very busy.

321
00:17:17,510 --> 00:17:18,780
Not at all.

322
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:23,110
This time, once you oust Chae Hwa Young
for breach of trust,

323
00:17:23,210 --> 00:17:24,520
Baek Ho and I...

324
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,750
will expose all the crimes
Chae Hwa Young has committed,

325
00:17:27,020 --> 00:17:29,320
and we'll make it so
she can't even breathe.

326
00:17:36,330 --> 00:17:37,360
CEO Chae Hwa Young.

327
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:38,530
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

328
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:42,530
It seems I will have to
have you dismissed as CEO.

329
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,700
What did you say?

330
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:51,010
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

331
00:17:51,710 --> 00:17:53,480
Though you're the majority shareholder,

332
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:56,610
you don't have the right
to just fire the CEO.

333
00:17:56,710 --> 00:17:59,450
Are you saying that because
you're unaware of the hotel's situation?

334
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:01,750
There are more than enough grounds
for dismissal...

335
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:03,150
due to your poor management.

336
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:05,390
On top of that, you took out a loan
with 50 percent interest paid upfront.

337
00:18:06,220 --> 00:18:07,890
Mr. Kim, the loan shark from Myeong-dong,

338
00:18:08,190 --> 00:18:10,490
sent a legal notice
to the hotel's Legal Team.

339
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:13,430
It says if you can't repay the money,
he'll bill the hotel.

340
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:16,400
- What?
- As the majority shareholder,

341
00:18:16,870 --> 00:18:20,340
it seems your management ability
is severely lacking.

342
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:23,070
How will you recover
the hotel's plummeting stock price?

343
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:24,510
Tell me.

344
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:27,540
So you're the majority shareholder.
Is that it?

345
00:18:28,010 --> 00:18:29,480
You still seem to have a lot to say,

346
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:31,680
but be prepared.

347
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,480
I can call an emergency
shareholders' meeting at any time...

348
00:18:33,820 --> 00:18:35,250
to have you dismissed.

349
00:18:41,290 --> 00:18:42,290
Kang Baek Ho.

350
00:18:43,230 --> 00:18:45,430
So that bastard is
the majority shareholder.

351
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:47,230
I'm so pissed.

352
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,240
Manager Lee.

353
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:56,810
Still no word from Martin Jang?

354
00:18:57,570 --> 00:18:59,510
When are you going to arrange the meeting?

355
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:03,510
(Staffing Services, Housekeeper)

356
00:19:31,710 --> 00:19:32,710
Welcome.

357
00:19:33,610 --> 00:19:34,810
Chairman Martin Jang.

358
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:37,250
I'm Chae Hwa Young, CEO of Dream Hotel.

359
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:44,150
Chairman Jang tends to skip
empty formalities like greetings.

360
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:45,560
He's difficult.

361
00:19:45,860 --> 00:19:48,460
But he does have a charisma
that reeks of money.

362
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:51,190
The Chairman doesn't speak any Korean.

363
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,600
I will be interpreting...

364
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:55,100
for all negotiations
and coordination today.

365
00:19:55,330 --> 00:19:56,330
I see.

366
00:19:57,100 --> 00:20:00,900
I apologize for bringing a person
of your stature to such a shabby place.

367
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:05,240
There are too many prying eyes,
so I had to meet in secret.

368
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,780
I hope you'll understand.

369
00:20:12,450 --> 00:20:13,450
Chae Hwa Young.

370
00:20:14,220 --> 00:20:15,520
Do you have any idea...

371
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:18,090
how much misery your endless greed
has brought upon my family?

372
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,090
I want nothing more
than to make you kneel...

373
00:20:21,090 --> 00:20:22,830
before Suk Hee and Jang Mi right now.

374
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:25,100
But just as Jang Mi said,

375
00:20:25,230 --> 00:20:28,370
I'll turn you into a beggar
and utterly destroy you.

376
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:35,570
He says to cut the pleasantries
and get straight to business.

377
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:36,840
Very well.

378
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:39,280
As you know, Chairman,

379
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:42,050
the operating rights for
Dream Hotel's casino and duty-free shop...

380
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,650
are the goose that lays the golden eggs.

381
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:47,050
I am offering
these prime, cash-generating businesses...

382
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:49,720
especially to you, Chairman.

383
00:20:58,530 --> 00:21:00,800
The Chairman says your offer
is just ridiculous.

384
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:03,270
He says it's a sinking ship
with a hole in its hull.

385
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,740
What good is it to take the casino
and duty-free shops from that?

386
00:21:06,270 --> 00:21:09,440
He says if you want a deal,
you'd better hand over the entire hotel.

387
00:21:09,710 --> 00:21:11,240
What do you mean, a sinking ship?

388
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,310
Isn't that incredibly rude to CEO Chae?

389
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,150
Manager Lee, that's enough.

390
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:18,450
My employee was rude.

391
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:21,120
But you know as well as I do...

392
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:22,720
that selling the entire hotel
is unreasonable.

393
00:21:23,090 --> 00:21:26,120
And it's not a decision
I can make on my own.

394
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:29,460
Dream Hotel is experiencing
temporary financial difficulty.

395
00:21:29,930 --> 00:21:33,500
But once we're over this hump,
we'll be right back on track.

396
00:21:43,610 --> 00:21:45,410
If you really don't want
to sell the entire hotel,

397
00:21:45,710 --> 00:21:47,310
he says to hand over...

398
00:21:47,310 --> 00:21:48,780
complete managerial control
of the hotel to the Chairman.

399
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:50,050
Excuse me?

400
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:52,350
You want me to become just a figurehead...

401
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:54,720
with no real power?

402
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:57,450
That's absolutely not happening.

403
00:22:06,660 --> 00:22:09,570
He's asking how you can still talk big
when you're cornered.

404
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:12,070
Chairman Martin Jang
says he will be leaving now.

405
00:22:14,810 --> 00:22:15,910
No. Wait...

406
00:22:16,570 --> 00:22:17,910
You can't leave.

407
00:22:17,910 --> 00:22:19,880
You can't just leave like this.

408
00:22:26,380 --> 00:22:27,420
Detective Lee.

409
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,320
Oh Jang Mi?

410
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:34,860
Detective Lee, you must be tired.

411
00:22:35,130 --> 00:22:38,130
We brought you a little something
to perk you up.

412
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:46,300
What's this? You shouldn't have.

413
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:54,710
What is this?

414
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:00,350
Take a look.

415
00:23:20,540 --> 00:23:22,070
This...

416
00:23:22,140 --> 00:23:25,240
So you've been taking money
and backing Chae Hwa Young all this time.

417
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:27,210
You even stole the evidence,

418
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:29,180
the wrench and the audio file,
from Shin Ae Ran,

419
00:23:29,250 --> 00:23:31,150
and delivered it right to Chae Hwa Young.

420
00:23:31,950 --> 00:23:33,480
No.

421
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:35,690
This is a misunderstanding.

422
00:23:35,690 --> 00:23:36,690
Hey!

423
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:38,090
Don't give me that
"misunderstanding" crap.

424
00:23:38,260 --> 00:23:39,390
Should I send this video...

425
00:23:39,390 --> 00:23:41,320
to Internal Affairs
at headquarters right now?

426
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:44,060
Accepting bribes, destroying evidence,
dereliction of duty...

427
00:23:44,230 --> 00:23:46,060
You won't just lose your badge,
you'll go straight to jail.

428
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:47,100
Wait!

429
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:49,130
Please, spare me.

430
00:23:50,170 --> 00:23:52,970
No, I'll do whatever you say. Please.

431
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:54,910
Just don't let me lose my badge.

432
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:57,210
Then...

433
00:23:57,610 --> 00:23:59,880
report any information to us first
from the investigation...

434
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:02,010
that goes to Chae Hwa Young.

435
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:06,350
And remember that we hold your leash now,
not Chae Hwa Young.

436
00:24:09,150 --> 00:24:10,590
If you cover for Chae Hwa Young again,

437
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:12,460
you'd better be prepared
for the consequences.

438
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:27,640
Looks like we've completely cut off
Detective Lee's support, right?

439
00:24:28,070 --> 00:24:29,070
Yes.

440
00:24:30,170 --> 00:24:32,340
Still no nibbles from the nurse, though.

441
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,810
We have to find and catch
whoever caused Seo Rin’s death...

442
00:24:35,410 --> 00:24:37,280
and make them pay for their crimes.

443
00:24:39,020 --> 00:24:41,920
(One-On-One Chat Inquiry:
Seeking Late-Night Surgical Assistant)

444
00:24:47,290 --> 00:24:50,490
Do you think the nurse from that hospital
might not have seen this post?

445
00:24:51,130 --> 00:24:52,300
She'll show up.

446
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:54,800
There's a warrant out for her,
so she can't apply for other hospitals,

447
00:24:54,870 --> 00:24:56,170
and her escape funds must have run out.

448
00:24:56,900 --> 00:25:00,670
There's no way she'd pass up our bait
of 5,000 dollars in cash with no ID check.

449
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,170
Let's just wait a little longer.

450
00:25:07,780 --> 00:25:10,510
Is the late-night surgical assistant job
still available?

451
00:25:10,810 --> 00:25:12,350
I can leave immediately.

452
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:15,020
Is the same-day cash payment
after surgery guaranteed?

453
00:25:15,820 --> 00:25:17,150
In 30 minutes, go to the back alley...

454
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:18,360
behind the abandoned building
in Yeongpa-dong.

455
00:25:18,790 --> 00:25:20,960
A black van with its hazard lights on
will be waiting.

456
00:25:22,860 --> 00:25:24,360
Okay, I'll do it.

457
00:25:25,100 --> 00:25:27,500
I don't know if it's the nurse,
Kim Yun Kyung,

458
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:28,670
but I'll go meet her and see.

459
00:25:29,270 --> 00:25:31,230
I can't let you go alone.
I'm going with you.

460
00:25:31,770 --> 00:25:32,770
Let's go.

461
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,240
That's her, right?

462
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:42,710
Yes, it is.

463
00:25:42,710 --> 00:25:43,880
Be careful.

464
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:54,420
Let go of me.

465
00:25:55,230 --> 00:25:58,190
Where are you going?
Shouldn't you be heading into surgery?

466
00:25:58,260 --> 00:26:00,760
You sure came running
when I mentioned 5,000 dollars in cash.

467
00:26:00,830 --> 00:26:02,100
I don't know anything.

468
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:03,700
You have the wrong person.

469
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:05,140
We have footage of you...

470
00:26:05,140 --> 00:26:07,470
wearing a smartwatch
in Ma Seo Rin's operating room.

471
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,170
Hand it over. Now.

472
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:10,770
A smartwatch?

473
00:26:11,410 --> 00:26:12,640
I don't have one.

474
00:26:13,210 --> 00:26:14,810
I'm telling you,
you've got the wrong person.

475
00:26:15,510 --> 00:26:16,550
Detective Oh.

476
00:26:25,620 --> 00:26:26,760
I'm Detective Oh.

477
00:26:30,490 --> 00:26:31,590
Nurse Kim Yun Kyung.

478
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,760
Violation of the Medical Service Act...

479
00:26:36,670 --> 00:26:38,030
Aiding and abetting a fugitive...

480
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,700
and for concealing a murder
and destroying evidence.

481
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,040
You're under emergency arrest.

482
00:26:42,410 --> 00:26:44,070
You have the right to an attorney.

483
00:26:44,070 --> 00:26:46,180
- Anything you say...
- Please, spare me.

484
00:26:46,540 --> 00:26:48,080
I didn't do it.

485
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:49,510
I swear, I didn't know anything.

486
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:53,450
Here, take the smartwatch.
Please, just let me go this once.

487
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:07,930
The doors are closing.

488
00:27:19,010 --> 00:27:20,010
Mom.

489
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:24,080
I'm shaking, and I'm cold.

490
00:27:24,910 --> 00:27:25,980
It's okay.

491
00:27:26,350 --> 00:27:28,020
You won't feel a thing
once the anesthesia kicks in.

492
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:33,020
You'll wake up prettier than Oh Jang Mi,
so don't you worry.

493
00:27:33,490 --> 00:27:36,490
You'll be the Ma Seo Rin you used to be,
so just hang in there.

494
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:38,060
But...

495
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,560
why am I so scared?

496
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,700
What is this?

497
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:44,600
That's my voice.

498
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:46,570
That's Seo Rin's voice.

499
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:21,440
(The First Man)

500
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:23,770
Her debt must be up to 200 million by now.

501
00:28:23,970 --> 00:28:26,780
From now on, don't give Chae Hwa Young
any room to breathe.

502
00:28:27,010 --> 00:28:30,080
If the 300-million-dollar kickback
I demanded...

503
00:28:30,150 --> 00:28:32,520
causes legal issues
and the deal is nullified,

504
00:28:32,650 --> 00:28:36,150
I will forfeit my 10 percent share
as a penalty.

505
00:28:36,290 --> 00:28:39,120
- I'm so scared. Help me.
- What is this?

